quizzes.question:
What is the output of this code?
import java.util.HashSet;
class A {
   public static void main(String[ ] args) {
   HashSet<String> set = new HashSet<String>();
   set.add("A");
   set.add("B");	
   set.add("C");
   System.out.println(set.size());
   }
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Sets[/h1]

A [b]Set [/b]is a collection that cannot contain duplicate elements. It models the mathematical set abstraction.
One of the implementations of the Set is the [b]HashSet [/b]class.
[b]Example:[/b] [code format="java" codeId="797"][b]import java.util.HashSet;[/b]

public class MyClass {
  public static void main(String[ ] args) {
    [b]HashSet[/b]<String> set = new [b]HashSet[/b]<String>();
    set.add("A");
    set.add("B");
    set.add("C");
    System.out.println(set);
  }
}
//  Output: [A, B, C][/code]
[note]You can use the [b]size[/b]() method to get the number of elements in the HashSet.[/note]
